WEBVTT

00:01.090 --> 00:02.876
Previously on
the <i>"Secret Circle"...</i>

00:02.877 --> 00:04.838
Demons.

00:04.938 --> 00:06.788
Evil entities.
Possession.

00:06.996 --> 00:10.480
Using snakes and insects
as vessels for dark energy.

00:10.482 --> 00:12.699
Demons need human form
to be fully active.

00:13.702 --> 00:15.169
John Blackwell
knows more about

00:15.171 --> 00:16.720
the hunters
than any of us.

00:16.722 --> 00:19.039
If Blackwell's such a huge force
of dark magic,

00:19.041 --> 00:21.374
why didn't he do anything
to stop the witch hunters?

00:21.376 --> 00:23.343
His power was stripped,
like all our parents.

00:23.345 --> 00:25.696
With or without power,
your father can help us.

00:25.698 --> 00:27.181
Eben will be back.

00:27.183 --> 00:29.850
What you did
unleashed a curse.

00:29.852 --> 00:32.019
Birds are a harbinger.

00:32.021 --> 00:34.054
A sign that the curse
has been activated.

00:34.056 --> 00:35.505
If you awaken
the curse,

00:35.507 --> 00:37.608
someone in your circle
will die.

00:37.610 --> 00:39.610
Found a recipe
for an elixir.

00:39.612 --> 00:40.748
When we drink this,

00:40.773 --> 00:42.694
we'll forget how we
feel about each other.

00:44.949 --> 00:48.068
I still love him,
but he doesn't love me.

00:48.070 --> 00:50.020
The elixir really
worked on Adam.

00:54.175 --> 00:55.742
Dude.

00:56.711 --> 00:58.729
All right.
Here's for you.

00:58.731 --> 01:01.098
And here's yours.

01:05.853 --> 01:08.555
Aah!
Heh.

01:08.557 --> 01:10.107
Hi.

01:10.109 --> 01:11.441
Hey.

01:12.560 --> 01:13.977
So, you're like
an old pro.

01:13.979 --> 01:16.263
Well, I learned
from the best.

01:17.598 --> 01:20.384
You taught me how
to hold the tray.

01:20.386 --> 01:22.035
You still remember
that, right?

01:22.037 --> 01:26.039
Yeah,
of course I do.

01:28.209 --> 01:29.743
Yeah. It just

01:29.745 --> 01:31.745
feels like
the whole...

01:31.747 --> 01:34.381
different time.
Different us.

01:34.383 --> 01:36.934
You know?

01:36.936 --> 01:40.304
Um, I should--
I should go.

01:40.306 --> 01:41.888
I'll see you later.

01:44.259 --> 01:47.644
I can't look away. It's like
an emotional car crash.

01:47.646 --> 01:49.056
Except they both don't
know they're the victims.

01:49.081 --> 01:49.897
So big deal.

01:49.898 --> 01:51.465
They loved each other.

01:51.467 --> 01:53.150
And then,
they drank one potion,

01:53.152 --> 01:54.768
and now, it's like
they never felt anything.

01:54.770 --> 01:56.136
Don't you think
that's tragic?

01:56.138 --> 01:58.355
Tragic was the way
Adam followed

01:58.357 --> 02:00.757
her dark highness around
like a puppy dog.

02:00.759 --> 02:02.075
He's better off.

02:02.077 --> 02:03.493
Faye, they sacrificed
their love

02:03.495 --> 02:05.478
so one of us
wouldn't die.

02:05.480 --> 02:07.314
Show
a little gratitude.

02:07.316 --> 02:08.865
I'm grateful...

02:08.866 --> 02:11.868
That I never have to see Adam
bat his oversized lashes

02:11.870 --> 02:14.655
at her undersized head
ever again.

02:14.657 --> 02:17.424
Sorry for the wait.

02:17.426 --> 02:19.593
Are you ok?

02:19.595 --> 02:23.663
I just--the whole thing
with Adam must be so horrible.

02:23.665 --> 02:27.100
Oh, no, no.
I'm fine.

02:27.102 --> 02:29.502
Yeah. I mean,
it's just kind of like

02:29.504 --> 02:31.305
seeing your ex
and forgetting why

02:31.307 --> 02:33.506
you ever had feelings for
for them.

02:33.508 --> 02:35.942
I mean, it's
more confusing than sad.

02:35.944 --> 02:38.528
I forgot to ask you.

02:38.530 --> 02:41.315
All of you, actually.

02:41.317 --> 02:44.117
You want to earn
some deep appreciation

02:44.119 --> 02:45.969
and make a little money
on the side?

02:45.971 --> 02:47.904
You lost me at
appreciation.

02:47.906 --> 02:50.540
The hockey team is having
their awards dinner

02:50.542 --> 02:53.043
at the boathouse tomorrow,
and I need extra servers.

02:53.045 --> 02:54.578
What do you think?

02:54.580 --> 02:57.214
I'd love to, but I'm a little
waitressed out.

02:57.216 --> 02:58.832
Thanks, though.

03:01.469 --> 03:03.387
Come on.

03:03.389 --> 03:05.005
What about you guys?

03:05.007 --> 03:06.473
Seriously.
My dad can't be there,

03:06.475 --> 03:07.674
and I need
some extra hands.

03:07.676 --> 03:09.726
- Is he ok?
- My dad?

03:09.728 --> 03:12.879
Oh, I think so.

03:12.881 --> 03:15.349
I don't know.
He's just been...

03:15.351 --> 03:18.318
kind of freaked out since
Cassie's dad showed up.

03:18.320 --> 03:20.020
Yeah,
he's actually a mess.

03:20.022 --> 03:22.939
And I lost a girlfriend,
Jake almost died,

03:22.941 --> 03:25.575
and the witch hunters are more
excited about killing us than ever.

03:25.577 --> 03:29.079
So it's real fun having
Blackwell back from the dead.

03:29.081 --> 03:32.565
I'll do it. Boys hockey team?
That might be fun.

03:32.567 --> 03:34.000
I'm not into
slave labor.

03:34.002 --> 03:35.786
It's $10 an hour

03:35.788 --> 03:37.587
plus a basket
of chicken wings.

03:37.589 --> 03:39.256
Eww. 15.

03:39.258 --> 03:41.875
Done. Thank you.

03:41.877 --> 03:43.877
I appreciate it.

03:45.880 --> 03:48.765
That poor guy.
Cassie can't even be around him.

03:48.767 --> 03:50.384
It's tragic.

03:50.386 --> 03:52.085
Tragic is not
asking for 20.

